ical vignettes with rabbinic, midrashic, and anthropological insights; by exploring Sephardi and Ashkenazi traditions as well as modern ideologies; and by bringing into sharp relief the activities of women and relations with Gentile neighbors. As such, this book provides a unique window on the particulars—and the significance—of personal and communal acts of identification among Jews past, present, and future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aFasts and feastsxJudaism. 0aJewish way of life. 0aJudaismxCustoms and practices. 0aLife cycle, HumanxReligious aspectsxJudaism. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh  aamerican jews.  aatonement.  abar mitzvah.  abat mitzvah.  ablessings.  aceremony.  acircumcision.  acoming of age.  acommunity.  adeath.  aeducation.  afaith.  afasts.  afeasts.  afolk tradition.  afolklore.  agrief.  ahanukah.  ahasidim.  ahenna.  aholidays.  ajewish culture.  ajewish holidays.  ajewish life.  ajudaica.  ajudaism.  akosher.  alife cycle.  aloss.  amarriage.  amourning.  anaming.  anonfiction.  apassover.  apilgrimage.  areligion.  areligious belief.  areligious identity.  areligious practices.  aremembering.  arites.  aritual.  asorrow.  asynagogue.  atorah.  atradition.  awimpel.  ayom kippur.  azionism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052091838240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520918382423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520918382/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles